# Agent protocols enforcement (gtcx-core)

> **Normative hub:** `gtcx-docs/docs/governance/protocols/`  
> **Local enforcement:** `docs/agents/agent-protocols-enforcement.md`  
> **Gate:** `pnpm agent:protocols:check` (CI + governance)

## Mandatory startup phases

| Phase | Protocol | You must |
| ----- | -------- | -------- |
| 5.4 | P22 Work Selection | Run `pnpm agent:next-work`; never ask operator to pick backlog when roadmap exists |
| 5.5 | P24 Coordination | Read `baseline-os/.../coordination-report-latest.md`; durable handoffs if blocked |
| 5.6 | P26 + P28 | Issue Proceed Brief (`docs/operations/agent-proceed-brief-template.md`); state authority class **S**, **A**, or **R** |
| 5.7 | P27 Execution | Run applicable V-ladder commands **in this session**; report **command + exit code** |

P27 detail: `.cursor/rules/protocol-27-agent-execution-obligation.mdc`

## Forbidden (P27)

- Deferring verification to the human (“verify locally”, “run in your terminal and paste output”)
- Story menus when Protocol 22 manifest exists

## Before claiming done

Run every applicable gate from `AGENTS.md` §7. Report failures with exit codes. If sandbox blocks a command, emit **Permission Unblock Report** and re-run when unblocked.
